'''Anita Manning''' (born 1 December 1947) is a [[Scotland|Scottish]] [[antiques]] expert and television personality from [[Glasgow]].<ref name=sundayhongkong>{{cite news|url=https://www.sundaypost.com/in10/antiques-road-trip-expert-anita-manning-reckons-theres-no-beating-hectic-hong-kong/ |title=Antiques Road Trip expert Anita Manning reckons there’s no beating hectic Hong Kong |date=25 January 2015 |work=[[Sunday Post]] |place=[[Dundee]] |accessdate=8 March 2016}}</ref> She is well known for her appearances as an expert and presenter on the [[BBC]]'s ''[[Bargain Hunt]]'', ''[[Flog It!]]'' and the ''[[Antiques Road Trip]]''. She is claimed to be the first female auctioneer in Scotland.<ref name=sundayhongkong />

==Career==
Manning's father used to take her to auctions on [[Sauchiehall Street]], in [[Glasgow]] and she grew to love antiques. She first got into the antiques business in the 1970s after buying a bed from an Irish dealer. He offered her a job as a buyer.{{citation needed|date=March 2016}}

After studying [[physical education]] and specialising in dance at [[Aberdeen]] and [[Edinburgh]], Manning was a teacher before she got married and had children. As a young mother, she developed a knowledge of antiques by buying furniture from auctions. After her first visit to Glasgow as a buyer, she bought and sold furniture in England and [[Ireland]] for about three years, driving all around the country in a truck.<ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b006mk0g/profiles/anita-manning BBC One - Flog It! - Anita Manning<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

Along with her daughter Lala, Manning has run the Glasgow auction house, Great Western Auctions, since 1989.<ref>[http://www.greatwesternauctions.com/about_us.php About Us], The Great Western Auctions. Retrieved 8 March 2016.</ref> Manning's son lives in [[Hong Kong]], while her mother lived in [[Australia]] for the last 35 years of her life.<ref name=sundayhongkong />

In 2016 Manning set a new record for the largest profit on a single item on the ''Antiques Road Trip''. A [[Buddharupa|Buddha statue]] she had purchased for £50 sold for £3,800, a 7,500% profit.<ref>[https://www.thesun.co.uk/news/1727745/lucky-dealer-makes-7500-profit-after-selling-buddha-statue-for-3800-on-new-antiques-road-trip-series/ GOOD KARMA Lucky dealer makes 7,500% profit after selling Buddha statue for £3,800 on new Antiques Road Trip series], The Sun, 5 September 2016</ref>

