In 2004, Kipchoge won a bronze medal at the [[Athletics at the 2004 Summer Olympics – Men's 5000 metres|5000 m final]] at the [[2004 Summer Olympics|2004 Athens Olympics]], behind El Guerrouj and [[Kenenisa Bekele]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rediff.com/sports/2004/aug/29oly-ath.htm|title=El Guerrouj completes historic double|date=29 August 2004|accessdate=27 April 2016|website=[[Rediff.com]]}}</ref> He also won the [[Trofeo Alasport]] cross country race earlier that season.

Kipchoge won the bronze in the 3000 metres indoor at the [[2006 IAAF World Indoor Championships|2006 World Championships]] in Moscow. At the end of the year, he ran at the [[San Silvestre Vallecana]] New Year's Eve 10&nbsp;km road race and he just held off [[Zersenay Tadese]] to win in a time of 26:54 minutes. This was better than the world record, but the time was assisted by the downhill course.<ref>{{cite news|date=1 January 2007|url=http://www.iaaf.org/news/news/kipchoge-breaks-27-minute-barrier-in-madrid-|title=Kipchoge breaks 27 minute barrier in Madrid|publisher=IAAF|accessdate=27 April 2016}}</ref>

Kipchoge won a silver medal at the 5000 m final of the [[2007 World Championships in Athletics|2007 World Championships]] at [[Osaka]] in 13:46.00, behind [[Bernard Lagat]] (13:45.87).<ref>2007 World Championships,
 {{cite web
 |url         = http://osaka2007.iaaf.org/results/gender=M/discipline=5000/combCode=hash/roundCode=f/result.html
