'''Nadine Chahine''' (in Arabic: نادين شاهين) is a [[Lebanese people|Lebanese]] [[Font|type]] designer working as the [[Arabic]] Specialist at Linotype and Monotype Imaging.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Lješnjanin|first1=Iris|title=Inside Creative Minds: Workflows, Habits and Strategies|date=2014|publisher=Smashing Magazine|isbn=978-3-944540-34-4|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Qs1nAwAAQBAJ&lpg=PT80&dq=Nadine%20Chahine&pg=PT80#v=onepage&q&f=false|chapter=The Art and Craft of Arabic Type Design}}</ref><ref name="Nadine Chahine in conversation with Catherine Dixon">{{cite web|last1=Dixon|first1=Catherine|title=Nadine Chahine in conversation with Catherine Dixon|url=https://www.myfonts.com/newsletters/cc/201607.html|website=[[MyFonts]]|accessdate=7 August 2016}}</ref> Her typeface Koufiya was the first to include a simultaneously designed matching Arabic and Latin parts.

Nadine Chanine was selected as one (69th) of the 100 most creative people ranked by ''[[Fast Company (magazine)|Fast Company]]'' magazine.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lipinski|first1=Jed|title=The 100 Most Creative People in Business 2012|url=http://www.fastcompany.com/3018253/most-creative-people-2012/69-nadine-chahine|work=Fast Company|date=April 27, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Nadine Chahine Honored for Arabic Type Contributions|url=http://typophile.com/node/93127|work=Typophile|date=May 17, 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140713160140/http://typophile.com/node/93127|archivedate=July 13, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref>

