{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}} {{Use Indian English|date=May 2014}} {{Infobox person | name = Nushrat Bharucha | image = Nushrat Bharucha on the sets of India’s Next Superstars.jpg | caption = Bharucha at an event for ''[[Sonu Ke Titu Ki Sweety]]'' in 2018 | residence = Mumbai | nationality = Indian | occupation = Actress | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=y|1985|05|17}}<ref name="cintaa"/> | birth_place = [[Mumbai]], [[Maharashtra]], India | yearsactive = 2006–present }} '''Nushrat Bharucha''' (born 17 May 1985)<ref name="cintaa">{{cite web|title=Nushrat Bharucha|url=http://www.cintaa.net/membership/cintaa_profile/2575|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140409192316/http://www.cintaa.net/membership/cintaa_profile/2575|dead-url=yes|archive-date=2014-04-09|work=Cine and TV Artistes Association (CINTAA) }}</ref> is an Indian film actress who has played the lead female role in several [[Bollywood|Hindi films]], including ''[[Love Sex Aur Dhokha]]'' (2010), ''[[Pyaar Ka Punchnama]]'' (2011), ''[[Akaash Vani]]'' (2013), ''[[Pyaar Ka Punchnama 2]]'' (2015), and ''[[Sonu Ke Titu Ki Sweety]]'' (2018). Nushrat Bharucha and [[Rajkumar Rao]] are to reunite for [[Hansal Mehta]]'s next social comedy drama [[Turram Khan]].
.<ref name="Society: Why we work">{{cite web|url=http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/5jOHGgIibrVolXCt4wxzdL/Society-Why-we-work.html|title=Society: Why we work}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gulfnews.com/life-style/celebrity/desi-news/bollywood/meet-the-sonu-ke-titu-ki-sweety-gang-1.2176880|title=Meet the ‘Sonu Ke Titu Ki Sweety’ gang}}</ref> Her father, Tanvir, is a businessman and her mother, Tasneem, is a homemaker. She has one younger brother, Zain-ul-Bharucha, and an elder sister. In an interview with the ''[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]]'', Bharucha talked openly about her life as being a member of the Dawoodi Bohra community, and her role in it.<ref name="Society: Why we work"/>
== Career == Bharucha debuted in ''Jai Santoshi Maa'' directed by Ahemed Siddiqui and later Love Sex Aur Dhoka and shot to prominence with ''[[Pyaar Ka Punchnama]]'' (2011) produced by Wide Frame Wicked Pictures. The film was story of three bachelors who fall in love with three different girls. Bharucha plays one of the three girls, Neha, who is in a live-in relationship with her boyfriend, Rajat. She gained popularity as ‘Babu’, Rajat's nickname for her in the film. The film became a sleeper hit of the year with newcomers in the lead. It has now achieved a cult status among the youth. Nusrat's latest feature film, is [[Luv Ranjan]]’s [[Sonu Ke Titu Ki Sweety]]<ref>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sonu_Ke_Titu_Ki_Sweety</ref> released on 23 February 2018, [[Luv Ranjan]]’s ''[[Pyaar Ka Punchnama 2]]'', in which she was paired with her ''[[Pyaar Ka Punchnama]]'' co-star, [[Kartik Aaryan]].
Bharucha has also acted in the [[Yash Raj Films]] television series, ''[[Seven (Indian TV series)|Seven]]''. She has also appeared in many TV advertisements. She once mentioned in an interview with [[India Today]], "I have never been to an acting school and was trained at auditions."<ref>{{Cite web| title = Nushrat Bharucha pairs up with Sivaji in Telugu flick Taj Mahal| author = Priyanka Sood and Prachi Rege| work = India Today| date = 28 May 2011| accessdate = 7 May 2016| url = http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/nushrat-bharucha-transformation-in-pyaar-ka-punchnama/1/139614.html}}</ref>
